.TH NOIRWATCH 1 "November 2024" "Version 1.3.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
NoirWatch \- Monitor specified websites for changes and send notifications.

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B noirwatch
[\fIoptions\fR] [\fIurl\fR]...

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B NoirWatch
is a script that monitors specified websites for changes and sends notifications when changes are detected. It supports various notification methods and allows customization through a configuration file.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \--help
Display this help message.
.TP
.B \-V, \--version
Display the script version.
.TP
.B \-i, \--interval \fI<minutes>\fR
Set the interval between checks (default is 15 minutes).
.TP
.B \-t, \--threshold \fI<percentage>\fR
Set the threshold percentage for detecting changes. Higher values mean fewer notifications for minor changes (default: 0%).
.TP
.B \-c, \--config \fI<config_file>\fR
Specify a custom configuration file (default: $HOME/.noirwatchrc).
.TP
.B \-I, \--init
Initialize the configuration file.
.TP
.B \-f, \--force
Force initialize the configuration file if one exists.
.TP
.B \-s, \--show-config
Show the configuration settings.
.TP
.B \-S, \--show-config-file
Show the configuration file.
.TP
.B \-f, \--url-file \fI<file>\fR
Specify a file containing a list of URLs to monitor (default: $HOME/.noirwatch_urls).
.TP
.B \-U, \--list-urls
List all watched URLs.
.TP
.B \-C, \--clean
Delete all cached files.
.TP
.B \-b, \--background
Run the script in the background.
.TP
.B \-p, \--pushover
Send Pushover notifications.
.TP
.B \-a, \--api-token \fI<token>\fR
Specify the API token for Pushover notifications.
.TP
.B \-u, \--user-key \fI<key>\fR
Specify the user key for Pushover notifications.
.TP
.B \-d, \--desktop
Send desktop notifications using AppleScript.
.TP
.B \-v, \--verbose
Enable verbose output.
.TP
.B \-l, \--log
Log the log file to the screen.
.TP
.B \-o, \--output \fI<file>\fR
Specify a custom log file location.
.TP
.B \-L, \--log-level \fI<level>\fR
Set the log level (FATAL, ERROR, WARN, INFO, DEBUG).
.TP
.B \-K, \--killall
Kill all running instances of the script.
.TP
.B \-k, \--kill \fI<pid>\fR
Kill a specific instance of the script by PID.
.TP
.B \-P, \--list-pids
List all running instances of the script.

.SH URL THRESHOLD PREFIX
.TP
.B [INT]<url>
Specify a threshold for a specific URL. This overrides the global threshold setting.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B noirwatch \-i 10 \-t 5 https://example.com
Monitor https://example.com every 10 minutes and notify if changes exceed 5%.
.TP
.B noirwatch \-c /path/to/config \-U
Use a custom configuration file and list all watched URLs.
.TP
.B noirwatch \-b \-p \-a your_api_token \-u your_user_key https://example.com
Run in the background and send Pushover notifications for changes on https://example.com.

.SH FILES
.TP
.B $HOME/.noirwatchrc
Default configuration file.
.TP
.B $HOME/.noirwatch_urls
Default URL list file.
.TP
.B /tmp/noirwatch_cache
Directory to store all cache files.
.TP
.B /tmp/noirwatch_cache/noirwatch.log
Default log file.

